<GXX>Service management
 <WBX>nginx and php-fpm:
  <CXX>docker compose up -d
 <WBX>angular webpack dev server:
  <CXX>APPS="<YXX><app> ...<CXX>" docker compose up --force-recreate angular_dev_server -d

<GXX>One-offs
 <CXX>docker compose run --build --rm angular_node_modules
 <CXX>docker compose run --build --rm angular_app_build <YXX><app> [<base-href> [<other-args...>]]
 <CXX>docker compose run --build --rm php-composer

<GXX>Create starter projects (if starting without an existing project)
 <CXX>docker compose run --build --rm angular_create_starter <YXX><app>
 <CXX>docker compose run --build --rm laravel_create_starter

<GXX>Tail the logs: <CXX>docker compose logs nginx php-fpm angular_dev_server -f
<GXX>Interactive Terminal: <CXX>docker compose exec -it -u root <YXX><service><CXX> bash

Problems? You can always exit back to WSL and run <CXX>dcl reset<CLR>. Or:
<GXX>docker compose down --rmi all nginx php-fpm angular_dev_server; \
<GXX>docker compose up -d; \
<GXX>APPS="<YXX>...<GXX>" docker compose up --force-recreate angular_dev_server -d; \
<GXX>docker compose logs nginx php-fpm angular_dev_server -f

